// Problem: Given N, compute the sum of the number of divisors
// of all integers from 1 to N.
// i.e., sum_{i=1}^{N} d(i)  where d(i) = number of divisors of i
//
// Constraints: 1 <= N <= 10^6
// Input: Single integer N
// Output: Sum of divisor counts from 1 to N
//
// Example:
// Input: 5
// Output: 10
// Explanation: d(1)=1, d(2)=2, d(3)=2, d(4)=3, d(5)=2 → sum=10

