// Problem: Given an array arr of N integers and integer K,
// count pairs (i, j) where i < j and gcd(arr[i], arr[j]) == K.
//
// Constraints: 1 <= N <= 10^5, 1 <= arr[i] <= 10^6, 1 <= K <= 10^6
// Input: N K followed by arr[0..N-1]
// Output: Number of pairs with gcd exactly K
//
// Example:
// Input: 5 2
//        2 4 6 9 10
// Output: 4
// Pairs: (2,4)=2, (2,6)=2, (2,10)=2, (4,6)=2 → 4 pairs
// (4,10)=gcd=2 also! Let's recount: (2,4)=2,(2,6)=2,(2,10)=2,(4,6)=2,(4,10)=2,(6,10)=2 → 6? 
// No: (9,anything) gcd not 2. Check: (6,10)=gcd=2. So 6 pairs... test carefully.

